§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ An ‹involution› is a function $f: S → S$ such that
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f = f^{-1} ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ In other words, an involution is its own inverse. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ A function $f: S → S$ is an involution if and only if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(f(x)) = x \quad \text{for all } x ∈ S⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

